1
00:01:57,920 --> 00:01:59,280
Oh, yeah?

2
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:02,160
Then what language
do I have to speak to this auntie?

3
00:02:02,680 --> 00:02:04,240
Try barking.

4
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,280
But I don't know how to bark.

5
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,760
That's why we could never talk.

6
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,440
Mook! Are you calling me a dog?!

7
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:11,400
Stop!

8
00:02:21,040 --> 00:02:23,200
I'll finish in just a second.

9
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,720
I do this all the time.
Just trust my hands, okay?

10
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:28,760
Are you almost there?

11
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:43,400
But there's only one company
that seems to stand a chance against us.

12
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,160
Mook's husband's company, right?

13
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:50,280
If I'd known she'd be this evil,

14
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:52,080
I wouldn't have let you marry her.

15
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,240
What's past is past, Ma.

16
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,800
Why'd you come home alone? Where's Usa?

17
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:03,280
I left her in charge at the office.

18
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,880
And did you eat yet, son?

19
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,560
Yes, Ma. I should go get some rest.

20
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,240
Where are you going?

21
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,240
I'm leaving Kuk,

22
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,360
and I'm taking Kongkwan home
to live with my mom.

23
00:03:36,440 --> 00:03:38,160
Oh well,

24
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:41,240
you're such a workaholic
that you neglect your family.

25
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,320
No man could tolerate that.

26
00:03:44,840 --> 00:03:46,440
So he had to cheat on his wife,

27
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:49,640
who's working hard to build a life, Ma?

28
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,160
If you really think he's in the right,

29
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:54,360
then I've got nothing to say to you.

30
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:57,920
If you think
you can make it alone, go ahead.

31
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,120
We'll see about that.

32
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,800
Just make sure you leave empty-handed.

33
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:04,520
The company belongs to Kuk.

34
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:07,640
Don't you worry.

35
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,600
My daughter and I will leave empty-handed.

36
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:13,240
And I'll show you just how far I can go.

37
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,200
As for the company,

38
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,519
let's just say I did you a favor.

39
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,440
I hope you'll take good care of it.

40
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,520
Because one day,

41
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:24,920
we might become rivals.

42
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:31,040
You'll never defeat a dragon like Kuk.

43
00:04:40,120 --> 00:04:41,200
Damn you, Mook.

44
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,400
HOTEL RESERVATION FORMS
LIST OF HOTELS

45
00:05:11,440 --> 00:05:14,120
KRABI

46
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,440
Tawan, let's eat.

47
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:27,880
Here.

48
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:30,480
No. I want to wait for Mom.

49
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:33,320
Why isn't she home yet, Saifah?

50
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:37,480
She said she'd go shopping for a bit.

51
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,480
She'll be back soon.

52
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,120
Come on, let's eat.

53
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:19,680
A Round Trip Travel
has submitted their program, Mr. Thee.

54
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,040
They sure work fast.

55
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,160
Please email it to me.

56
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:28,120
It's quite late, Mr. Thee.

57
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,800
Why don't you do it tomorrow?

58
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,280
It's alright.

59
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,440
I want to see if I like their program.

60
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:37,400
Sure, sir.

61
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:19,920
Where on earth did I put my towel?

62
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:56,120
<i>Really, Mook?! I'm going to be a father?</i>

63
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,840
I'm so happy.

64
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,520
Mook, let's go tell Ma. She'd be so happy.

65
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:09,400
I have a meeting with a client today
to finalize the group tour.

66
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:12,320
How about we go tell her together
once the meeting's over?

67
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,440
Please?

68
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:15,960
Fine.

69
00:09:16,040 --> 00:09:17,400
Look.

70
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,240
What's up?

71
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,160
Mook.

72
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:27,480
It's late. You're still up?

73
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,760
You can go to bed.

74
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,680
I need to send our client a quotation.

75
00:09:31,760 --> 00:09:33,520
The wrap-up meeting's tomorrow.

76
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:36,320
Just sleep first.

77
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:39,440
Wait, Kuk! You moved everything!

78
00:09:39,520 --> 00:09:42,000
Can you leave me alone?
Can't you see I'm working?

79
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:48,880
Kuk.

80
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,320
I… Kuk.

81
00:09:54,320 --> 00:09:56,600
It's just my pregnancy hormones.

82
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,280
Kuk!

83
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:20,040
Okay, so we'll go over two groups today.

84
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:25,160
I like the design, but I think
the color could be changed a bit.

85
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:38,560
Let's not go home till we're drunk!

86
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,640
Let's go all out!

87
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:51,080
What's up, sweetie?

88
00:10:51,160 --> 00:10:52,680
She's sleeping so soundly, Mook.

89
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,440
Look at her face.

90
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:00,240
- I wonder who she looks like.
- Her father, of course!

91
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,360
She does look like you, a little bit.

92
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,960
Of course, the daughter
would look like her dad,

93
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,000
- right, honey?
- Right?

94
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:11,240
- Look at her.
- Her cheeks are so red.

95
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:12,800
What's up, honey?

96
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,600
She's sleeping so soundly.

97
00:11:58,680 --> 00:12:00,480
Come on. Cheers!

98
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:08,320
Are you having fun?

99
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,120
Yes.

100
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:12,160
Cheers.

101
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,240
Why does Mook

102
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,960
treat me like I don't matter?

103
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:29,600
I understand.

104
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:32,440
She has a good man like you by her side,

105
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:34,320
yet she's taking you for granted.

106
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,600
What are you doing?

107
00:12:56,920 --> 00:12:58,960
Do you still miss your family?

108
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:01,200
What?

109
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,720
Did seeing her face again
make you miss her that bad?

110
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:07,080
Usa, that's not it.

111
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:10,760
I just happened to find the rubber duck
when I opened the drawer.

112
00:13:12,760 --> 00:13:14,120
Then we're good.

113
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,880
Don't you dare think
about going back to Mook.

114
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,360
Everything fine at work?

115
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,600
Yes, it is.

116
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:27,200
I planned with the team
to use this project

117
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,960
to promote our business.

118
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,960
Don't you worry, Kuk.

119
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:34,240
We'll surely win against Mook on this one.

120
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,480
Oh, Usa.

121
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,440
Where did you put my towel?

122
00:13:50,920 --> 00:13:52,440
I'll go find it for you.

123
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:34,760
WAT PAKNAM BHASICHAROEN

124
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,760
If you're working this hard,
I'm sure we'll win.

125
00:14:56,840 --> 00:15:00,000
But for now, you should
go home and rest, Mook.

126
00:15:10,520 --> 00:15:12,640
You'll be hearing good news tomorrow.

127
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:13,600
I guarantee you!

128
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:17,160
Okay. I trust your skills, Mook.

129
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:28,040
We should grab some food
before you go home.

130
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:30,560
How about some late night rice soup?

131
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,200
- Deal.
- Okay, let's go!

132
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,360
Just a moment.

133
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,120
- Can I help you?
- Sure.

134
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:43,560
- Can I put this away?
- Yes, please.

135
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:51,240
YOU HAVE A NEW EMAIL

136
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,520
- It's here!
- It's here! The email!

137
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:56,040
We got the email! We got the email!

138
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,640
We got the email!

139
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:00,920
Please calm down.

140
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:04,800
- Hey!
- Mook!

141
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:07,440
- Mook, get over here! They just replied.
- Come here!

142
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,360
Really, Boss?

143
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,600
Let me see.

144
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:15,560
- Should I open it now?
- Yeah!

145
00:16:19,040 --> 00:16:20,360
Is this a sick joke?

146
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:22,000
Did we lose, Mook?

147
00:16:24,280 --> 00:16:26,000
Where are you going?

148
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:27,560
To The One.

149
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:31,040
Mook!

150
00:16:32,520 --> 00:16:34,160
‪The heck? Boss!

151
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:39,960
- His office, right?
- Uh, wait.

152
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,440
- Please wait a moment!
- I need to see Mr. Thee now!

153
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:44,280
- Let me tell him first!
- No!

154
00:16:44,360 --> 00:16:45,400
Please calm--

155
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,560
It's alright, Mr. Pitak.

156
00:16:57,600 --> 00:17:01,560
I'd like to know why you changed
my company's entire tour program.

157
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:10,640
It's all just to test

158
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,680
your company's ability to handle

159
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,480
and solve immediate problems

160
00:17:16,280 --> 00:17:19,720
or unforeseen circumstances.

161
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:25,480
If you can't do it, then it's over.

162
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,000
I'll choose your rival company.

163
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,000
So?

164
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:48,280
If you changed the program
to test my company's professionalism,

165
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:50,160
then I'm happy to oblige.

166
00:17:57,080 --> 00:17:58,560
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

167
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,560
I'd like to pick the guide for this trip.

168
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:11,280
The guide for this trip
has to be you only.

169
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,680
How unlucky can I get?

170
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:54,360
Oh, Mook!

171
00:18:59,480 --> 00:19:00,640
What a coincidence.

172
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,120
Are you here to see Mr. Thee too?

173
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:04,280
That's none of your business.

174
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:05,800
Why should I tell you?

175
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:08,560
Afraid of losing?

176
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,760
Is that why you came
to see him in private?

177
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:15,560
I'd never do stupid things like that.

178
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:18,840
But I don't doubt you would.

179
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:23,640
I just came to welcome him officially.

180
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,680
It's common courtesy.

181
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:27,280
You wouldn't get it.

182
00:19:30,080 --> 00:19:34,160
It's because I use
my brain to work, rather than…

183
00:19:35,360 --> 00:19:37,200
using my cleavage, like you do.

184
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,480
Let me guess.

185
00:19:39,560 --> 00:19:43,320
Family Tour and Travel probably hasn't
submitted anything for The One's task,

186
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,280
so you came looking for a shortcut.

187
00:19:46,880 --> 00:19:50,480
It doesn't matter what I use to work.

188
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:53,760
Come to think of it,

189
00:19:54,400 --> 00:19:55,760
I won against you once.

190
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:58,720
This time is no different.

191
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,960
Mr. Thee will surely choose me too.

192
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,600
I'm glad you're so confident.

193
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:07,000
Just do your best,

194
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:11,280
so I won't have to watch
the company I built fall apart.

195
00:20:22,160 --> 00:20:23,320
Why isn't it done yet?

196
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:25,320
And where's Usa?

197
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,280
I asked you where she is!

198
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:33,160
She said she's going to The One.

199
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:35,280
Why?

200
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:37,400
I'm not sure.

201
00:20:39,280 --> 00:20:41,000
Hurry and get it done.

202
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:44,280
Submit it to The One
before A Round Trip Travel does. Got it?

203
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:45,400
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

204
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:54,600
USA

205
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:10,280
Yesterday we had a briefing,
so I didn't get to talk to you.

206
00:21:10,360 --> 00:21:13,840
And I wanted to officially
welcome you again today

207
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:15,720
and also introduce myself.

208
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:21,520
Family Tour and Travel is looking forward
to working with The One.

209
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:33,320
You really shouldn't have.

210
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,840
Submitting your work would've sufficed.

211
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:42,480
Mr. Thee isn't very good with formalities.

212
00:21:45,320 --> 00:21:47,840
If that is all, I’ll take my leave.

213
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:49,680
Pleased to meet you.

214
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:58,440
Submitting your plan earlier

215
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,880
would've been nicer than that gift basket.

216
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:04,680
Sure.

217
00:22:04,760 --> 00:22:07,480
I'll submit it
for your consideration soon.

218
00:22:20,120 --> 00:22:23,200
Mr. Thee is just straightforward.

219
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:25,720
I hope you don't mind.

220
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:27,720
Not at all.

221
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:28,960
I understand.

222
00:22:29,040 --> 00:22:32,320
I like a challenge anyway.

223
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:45,920
So why exactly did Mr. Thee change
your entire program?

224
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:49,040
To get back at me, of course.

225
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:52,760
What do you mean? I don't get it.

226
00:22:54,440 --> 00:22:58,800
The guy who asked for laundry fees
after I threw up on him is him.

227
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:01,440
Is that true, Mook?

228
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:03,600
It might sound like a coincidence,

229
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,000
but it's true.

230
00:23:06,080 --> 00:23:08,920
It just so happens
that he's rich, he's our client,

231
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,600
and we want this project, is all.

232
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:15,080
If that's the case,
he may be biased against us.

233
00:23:18,040 --> 00:23:20,960
If you feel uncomfortable,
we can skip this project

234
00:23:21,040 --> 00:23:22,720
and look for a new one.

235
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:23,800
No way, Boss.

236
00:23:23,880 --> 00:23:26,920
I'll prove to him
that silly pranks like that

237
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:28,320
do not work on me.

238
00:23:30,920 --> 00:23:32,320
Don't worry, Boss.

239
00:23:32,400 --> 00:23:35,760
I'll win this deal
for our company, no matter what.

240
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:45,120
HOW ABOUT AT THE COMPANY? THAI DESSERTS
THAI MASSAGE, DONATION AT ORPHANAGE

241
00:23:49,080 --> 00:23:50,400
If you're changing everything,

242
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:52,560
why not choose the locations
in the first place?

243
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,600
LIST OF DESTINATIONS

244
00:23:58,680 --> 00:23:59,560
ORPHANAGE, HOST CLUB

245
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:00,600
SILOM, NANA, THAI DESSERT SHOP

246
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:03,520
HOST CLUB

247
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:08,920
I knew it!

248
00:24:16,280 --> 00:24:19,320
I'm gonna teach you a lesson, kid.

249
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:33,800
Kongkwan, I need to see
Khim and Ploy tonight.

250
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,840
Just go to bed with Grandma, honey.

251
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,360
I'll give you a kiss once I'm home.

252
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:40,320
<i>Don't drink, Mommy. Don't drink and drive.</i>

253
00:24:41,760 --> 00:24:45,080
Roger that. Mommy won't drink for sure.
Don't worry.

254
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:47,440
Good night, honey. Mwah.

255
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:53,520
The joys of being a family woman.

256
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:56,080
Gotta call them everywhere you go.

257
00:24:56,160 --> 00:24:57,200
Unlike me.

258
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:58,200
I'm so free.

259
00:24:58,280 --> 00:25:00,400
I never have to call anyone when I go out.

260
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:04,160
Sounds like you've got nobody.

261
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:09,520
Or maybe you can't choose who to call yet.

262
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,680
You know me too well.

263
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:18,600
Why isn't Ploy here yet?

264
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:22,720
It's not unlike her to be late.

265
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:24,360
- Am I right?
- Yeah.

266
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:26,640
- Let's just eat it all.
- Can you reach it?

267
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,240
Sorry, guys.

268
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:32,240
My work wasn't done yet,
and it’s year-end closing time.

269
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:34,160
- Oh, boy.
- Watch your skirt.

270
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:35,720
I need to breathe.

271
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:37,440
Yeah. Catch your breath.

272
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:40,680
Okay.

273
00:25:41,360 --> 00:25:43,240
This is all you ordered?

274
00:25:43,840 --> 00:25:45,400
That's not nearly enough!

275
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:48,880
I'm starving to death here.
Can I order some more?

276
00:25:50,240 --> 00:25:51,680
Suit yourself.

277
00:25:51,760 --> 00:25:54,080
- I'm just so hungry.
- Sure.

278
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,200
Mook,

279
00:25:57,280 --> 00:26:00,760
I heard your company's pitching
for the big project too?

280
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:05,120
If we land this deal,
it'll keep us afloat for a while.

281
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:08,800
I don't care about that.

282
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:13,880
I only care about the CEO,
who's apparently a total stud.

283
00:26:15,120 --> 00:26:19,280
Well, did you also hear
that he's a total jerk?

284
00:26:19,360 --> 00:26:21,120
He's so snarky too.

285
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,520
It won't be easy.

286
00:26:28,040 --> 00:26:30,480
I'm up against Family Tour and Travel too.

287
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:35,480
Against Kuk, you mean?

288
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,760
Can he just burn in hell already?

289
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:43,040
When will he leave you alone?

290
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,960
Please don't be mad at me, Kuk.

291
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:10,280
I only did it for our company.

292
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:16,240
If we're on Mr. Thee's good side,
things will be easier.

293
00:27:17,720 --> 00:27:19,000
Can you swear on your life

294
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:22,880
what you did was only for our work?

295
00:27:26,600 --> 00:27:28,440
Even Mook went to see him too.

296
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:31,840
If I hadn't gone,
we'd be at a disadvantage.

297
00:27:31,920 --> 00:27:34,440
You're too naive
to keep up with her schemes.

298
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:37,400
Why did she go see him anyway?

299
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:39,680
Do you really have to ask?

300
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:42,760
These days, you need
to pull strings to do well in business.

301
00:27:42,840 --> 00:27:45,160
Seeing him in private like that…

302
00:27:45,680 --> 00:27:47,640
She must be scheming something.

303
00:27:51,200 --> 00:27:52,600
As for Mr. Thee,

304
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:55,520
I'm sure I can handle him. Mark my words.

305
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,520
I'll beat Mook, no matter what.

306
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:04,720
I won't let her call you a loser.

307
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:11,800
Thank you, Usa, for doing all this for me.

308
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,320
Let's go.

309
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:28,600
I just don't get it.

310
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:29,920
You've broken up.

311
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,760
Why can't he mind his own business?

312
00:28:32,360 --> 00:28:35,760
I think he's pitching
against you on purpose.

313
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,720
And why do you care, Khim?

314
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,480
I don't see Mook complaining one bit.

315
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:43,440
Let's stop talking about others.

316
00:28:43,520 --> 00:28:45,600
It'll only bring us down.

317
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,640
Hey, I have something important
to tell you.

318
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:52,520
But really, though,

319
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:55,560
he caused all kinds of problems
while you were together.

320
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:58,080
Now you've broken up,
yet he's still at it.

321
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,640
Speak of the devil.

322
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,480
So many coincidences today, Mook.

323
00:29:11,280 --> 00:29:13,720
Yeah, what a coincidence.

324
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:15,920
Speak of the devil and he appears.

325
00:29:16,560 --> 00:29:18,160
- Who are you calling the devil?
- Usa.

326
00:29:18,680 --> 00:29:19,720
Go ahead, then.

327
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:23,000
You hit me, I hit you back. Fair game.

328
00:29:25,600 --> 00:29:30,160
<i>Idam me ñātinam hotu, sukhitā hontu ñātayo</i>

329
00:29:35,560 --> 00:29:37,160
There, I've forgiven you.

330
00:29:37,240 --> 00:29:38,680
May you rest in peace.

331
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:39,760
‪Hey, Mook!

332
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,080
Would you stop it, Mook?

333
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:45,760
Stop acting this way.

334
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:48,560
This is exactly why we could never talk!

335
00:29:48,640 --> 00:29:49,800
So I have to be like her?

336
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:51,560
Is that how you can talk?

337
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:55,680
Also, there's no need
for us to talk anyway.

338
00:29:55,760 --> 00:29:56,760
- Mook!
- What?!

339
00:29:56,840 --> 00:29:59,320
Excuse me. Please don't fight.

340
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,760
Please lower your voice.

341
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:03,400
You're bothering others.

342
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,240
Usa, let's leave.

343
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:15,320
My apologies.

344
00:30:15,400 --> 00:30:17,360
I'll have someone
clean up the broken bowl.

345
00:30:17,440 --> 00:30:18,800
Thank you.

346
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:28,760
You okay, Mook?

347
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:39,880
I've lost my appetite. My mood's ruined.

348
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,680
Why'd we have to meet them?

349
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:44,720
It tastes great, though.

350
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,080
Look at you. What a mess!

351
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:49,920
Here.

352
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:52,360
You're acting like Kongkwan.

353
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:55,360
- Let me wipe it off.
- Like Kongkwan? Your daughter?

354
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,840
Keep it.

355
00:30:56,920 --> 00:30:58,960
- Keep it in case you need it.
- Mook.

356
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,920
Are you okay, Mook?

357
00:31:16,480 --> 00:31:18,840
Ever since the day
I found them together at a hotel,

358
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:22,360
I've always told myself

359
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:26,560
I'm no one important to Kuk anymore.

360
00:31:28,880 --> 00:31:30,720
For me,

361
00:31:30,800 --> 00:31:34,560
my love life has zero hope,
and marriage is hell.

362
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:38,480
Here, an invitation to my wedding!

363
00:31:39,080 --> 00:31:40,360
- Wedding?!
- Wedding?!

364
00:31:41,960 --> 00:31:43,240
I'm getting married.

365
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:44,760
My name?

366
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,960
Who is it?

367
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:50,440
"Udom"?

368
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:52,640
Who's that? You never mentioned him.

369
00:31:52,720 --> 00:31:54,920
He's the son of my dad's best friend.

370
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:58,040
When did you two start dating?

371
00:31:58,120 --> 00:31:59,000
How come we never knew?

372
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,360
I've never met him either.

373
00:32:02,600 --> 00:32:05,000
I met him once when my brother was little.

374
00:32:05,080 --> 00:32:06,080
On a Chinese New Year.

375
00:32:10,880 --> 00:32:11,960
Wait a second.

376
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,520
Are you telling me
it's an arranged marriage?

377
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,360
In this day and age?!

378
00:32:19,280 --> 00:32:21,400
I used to believe in love too,

379
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:23,040
but see what happened to Mook.

380
00:32:23,560 --> 00:32:25,320
He and she loved each other since college.

381
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:26,760
He was her first boyfriend.

382
00:32:26,840 --> 00:32:30,920
They got married,
had a kid, started a family,

383
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:32,720
built a fortune together and everything.

384
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:34,840
Yet still, they broke up.

385
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:38,880
Whether we love each other or not,
and whether it's arranged or not,

386
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:43,000
in the end, there's no guarantee
if your love life will fail or not.

387
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:46,520
But if you need to marry
someone you don't love,

388
00:32:46,600 --> 00:32:47,520
who you didn't choose,

389
00:32:47,600 --> 00:32:51,080
and without getting to know each other,
that can't be good, right?

390
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:53,880
Love needs to come from the heart.

391
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,680
Think this through, Ploy.

392
00:32:55,760 --> 00:32:59,320
We'll probably end up
loving each other after a while.

393
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:05,040
Sometimes love life
is just like buying lottery tickets.

394
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:08,640
You know what?

395
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:11,160
Come on.

396
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:13,640
Here's to Ploy and her wedding.

397
00:33:17,080 --> 00:33:21,040
I hope you win the jackpot
in the lottery, my friend.

398
00:33:23,360 --> 00:33:26,200
Hey, Khim! Come on!

399
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,280
Fine.

400
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:33,200
Whatever works for you, works for me.

401
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:34,280
Congrats, girl.

402
00:33:34,360 --> 00:33:37,800
I'm glad to have you both as my friends.

403
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:39,640
Thank you, you two.

404
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:41,760
Cheers.

405
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:45,320
- Yay!
- Yay!

406
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:09,520
Mr. Thee.

407
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:15,880
What's the matter, Mr. Thee?

408
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,000
<i>This is exactly why</i>

409
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,360
- <i>we could never talk!</i>
- That's Ms. Mook

410
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:26,280
- <i>So I have to be…</i>
- and

411
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:29,239
Mr. Apichart, the CEO
of Family Tour and Travel?

412
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:31,480
Is it some kind of bad blood?

413
00:34:32,600 --> 00:34:34,560
Looks like they had a fight
at a restaurant.

414
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,239
Well,

415
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:39,679
they're probably business rivals.

416
00:34:40,199 --> 00:34:43,520
After all, they work
in the same industry, Mr. Thee.

417
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,239
I want to learn about their past,

418
00:34:48,320 --> 00:34:50,239
see if they've got bad blood.

419
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:56,239
I just want to be aware
before I decide to work with them.

420
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,520
Of course. I'll look into it for you.

421
00:35:01,160 --> 00:35:03,600
And Family Tour and Travel's
submitted their program.

422
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:05,240
I emailed it to you.

423
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:09,160
Then, I'll start testing
the program and services

424
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:11,400
of A Round Trip Travel first.

425
00:35:11,480 --> 00:35:12,760
Please let them know.

426
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:14,440
Sure, sir.

427
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:37,280
That's your new outfit, May?

428
00:35:43,360 --> 00:35:44,520
Isn't it cute?

429
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:45,720
Yeah.

430
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:51,040
I'm going to see a client,
so I need a good first impression.

431
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:52,680
That's true.

432
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,280
- Are you impressed?
- Super.

433
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,880
- You like it?
- Yes.

434
00:35:57,440 --> 00:35:59,800
Mook, here's some coffee.

435
00:35:59,880 --> 00:36:02,400
Black coffee. Less sweet, but still sweet.

436
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,960
- Thank you.
- Of course.

437
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,080
Is everything prepared?

438
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:08,960
Yes. I've coordinated
with all the teams in the area.

439
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:10,840
- Good work. I'd better get going.
- Sure.

440
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,200
- Bye--
- Wait!

441
00:36:16,640 --> 00:36:18,200
<i>I forgot to tell you.</i>

442
00:36:18,280 --> 00:36:20,040
<i>I'd like to pick the guide for this trip.</i>

443
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:25,280
The guide for this trip
has to be you only.

444
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:26,520
Let's go.

445
00:36:28,640 --> 00:36:31,880
May, you don't have to go. I'll go alone.

446
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:34,040
Come on!

447
00:36:34,120 --> 00:36:37,400
I… bought a new outfit
just for this job! I'm so ready.

448
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:41,080
Well… I want you to stay here with Whan

449
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:43,800
and help collaborate
about the locations from this office.

450
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:45,160
‪Please.

451
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:52,520
Mook, will you really be fine on your own?

452
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:56,760
Of course! I'll show them who's boss.

453
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:57,680
I'm going now. Bye.

454
00:36:59,000 --> 00:36:59,840
Mook.

455
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:02,680
You got this!

456
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,880
- I got this!
- Good luck!

457
00:37:03,960 --> 00:37:05,000
Okay, bye.

458
00:37:14,680 --> 00:37:16,840
I'll have this, then.
Can you make a new one?

459
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:27,160
Good morning, Mr. Pitak.

460
00:37:27,240 --> 00:37:28,800
Good morning, Ms. Mook.

461
00:37:28,880 --> 00:37:30,400
This way, please.

462
00:37:31,200 --> 00:37:34,160
I'm not coming. Mr. Thee will go alone.

463
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,640
And where is he?

464
00:38:05,480 --> 00:38:07,040
Good morning, Mr. Thee.

465
00:38:07,120 --> 00:38:08,080
This way, please.

466
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:10,240
No. I'm going in my car.

467
00:38:10,960 --> 00:38:11,960
You can drive, right?

468
00:38:13,520 --> 00:38:15,360
I can, but I--

469
00:38:19,560 --> 00:38:20,520
It's fine.

470
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:22,520
I found a driver for the day.
You can take a rest.

471
00:38:31,880 --> 00:38:33,240
Excuse me.

472
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:35,960
Can I cancel your service for today?
You can leave.

473
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:38,320
- Sure, ma'am.
- I'll handle the payment later.

474
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,320
May I grab my stuff?

475
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:44,080
Thank you. I'm very sorry.

476
00:39:18,320 --> 00:39:20,360
Oh, Mr. Thee.

477
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:23,640
You aren't letting her off easy, are you?

478
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:35,120
Mr. Thee, this angle's perfect.

479
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:36,280
Let me take a picture for you.

480
00:39:36,360 --> 00:39:37,320
One…

481
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:47,600
Wat Saket was originally known
as Wat Sakae.

482
00:39:47,680 --> 00:39:50,280
It's an ancient temple
originated in the Ayutthaya era.

483
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:51,960
During King Rama I's reign,

484
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:55,600
His Majesty ordered its renovation
and the excavation of a canal around it,

485
00:39:55,680 --> 00:39:57,720
then renamed it

486
00:39:57,800 --> 00:40:01,120
to Wat Saket, which means
"to wash one's hair."

487
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:05,840
And here's a view of the temple grounds.

488
00:40:13,080 --> 00:40:16,360
That's called the Phu Khao Thong,
or the Golden Mount,

489
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:17,800
which…

490
00:40:18,320 --> 00:40:21,320
is a pagoda built
on top of a man-made hill.

491
00:40:23,720 --> 00:40:24,840
Mr. Thee.

492
00:40:27,840 --> 00:40:31,200
Mr. Thee, please take an umbrella.

493
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:41,760
Why don't you open it?

494
00:40:44,160 --> 00:40:46,280
Mr. Thee, please wait!

495
00:40:49,080 --> 00:40:52,240
Please be careful. Mr. Thee!

496
00:40:58,320 --> 00:40:59,360
Mr. Thee,

497
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:01,720
please be careful.

498
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:09,800
Please go ahead, Mr. Thee.

499
00:41:19,360 --> 00:41:20,320
Go on ahead.

500
00:41:31,400 --> 00:41:34,920
There's also a rest stop up ahead
which is their coffee shop, Mr. Thee.

501
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,920
I haven't mentioned,
but the stairs have 144 steps,

502
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:42,400
and you can…

503
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:46,400
You can also ring the bells, Mr. Thee.

504
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:50,560
Want to try it?

505
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:56,320
Please go right ahead.

506
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:58,120
Would you like a picture?

507
00:42:00,280 --> 00:42:01,400
Mr. Thee,

508
00:42:01,920 --> 00:42:05,920
from this angle, if you stop here,
you'll get a full view of Bangkok.

509
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:08,520
And that is the Loha Prasat…

510
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:11,560
Mr. Thee!

511
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:18,400
Mr. Thee, from this angle,

512
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:20,800
you can get a full view
of the surroundings,

513
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:23,720
and more importantly, a view of Bangkok.

514
00:42:23,800 --> 00:42:26,160
There's Pratunam.

515
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:27,680
And there's also the Bobae Market.

516
00:42:27,760 --> 00:42:31,160
They're both wholesale hubs
that many foreigners love.

517
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:35,440
Mr. Thee… Mr. Thee!

518
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:38,040
This angle's perfect.

519
00:42:38,120 --> 00:42:39,360
Let me take a picture for you.

520
00:42:39,440 --> 00:42:41,960
One, two, thre…

521
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:57,720
During King Rama IV's reign,

522
00:42:57,800 --> 00:43:00,920
Phu Khao Thong was later renamed
to Borommabanphot.

523
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:04,920
At the top,
the Buddha's relics are enshrined inside.

524
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:07,160
You may head up there
and pay your respects.

525
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:11,360
No need to take off your shoes,
Mr. Thee. Be careful.

526
00:43:14,520 --> 00:43:16,240
Isn't he tired at all?

527
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:20,200
Here are the flowers,
incense, and candles.

528
00:43:43,800 --> 00:43:45,280
There are many types of <i>tungs.</i>

529
00:43:45,360 --> 00:43:48,720
The one I hung just now
is a <i>tung</i> of the 12 star signs,

530
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:50,320
or the 12 zodiac signs,

531
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:53,760
which is made of <i>saa</i> paper,
with the 12 zodiac signs printed on it.

532
00:43:53,840 --> 00:43:56,200
It is believed that by offering a <i>tung</i>,

533
00:43:56,280 --> 00:43:58,800
you bring blessings
to yourself and your family.

534
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:01,040
And these are called Lanna lanterns.

535
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:02,720
It is believed that

536
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:05,640
they can bring blessings
and light to your family.

537
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:08,200
BREWED COFFEE SHOP

538
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:10,040
Excuse me.

539
00:44:10,120 --> 00:44:12,640
Can you buy some of my snacks?

540
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:14,960
Let's see. What do we have here?

541
00:44:15,480 --> 00:44:17,720
I'll have this one, then.

542
00:44:19,040 --> 00:44:19,920
Here you go.

543
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:22,400
I don't have change.

544
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:23,960
That's alright.

545
00:44:24,040 --> 00:44:27,000
Keep the change and treat yourself
with meals and snacks.

546
00:44:27,080 --> 00:44:28,680
Thank you.

547
00:44:41,480 --> 00:44:44,000
Mr. Thee, here's your iced coffee.

548
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:48,360
Let's hurry. We've got two more stops.

549
00:44:49,320 --> 00:44:51,240
What about your coffee?

550
00:44:51,320 --> 00:44:53,280
Mr. Thee, please wait!

551
00:44:56,760 --> 00:44:57,800
Mr. Thee!

552
00:44:58,400 --> 00:44:59,440
Of course.

553
00:44:59,520 --> 00:45:02,080
Our team at Family Tour will do our best.

554
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:03,600
Yes.

555
00:45:03,680 --> 00:45:04,880
Thank you.

556
00:45:08,520 --> 00:45:09,680
Usa,

557
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:12,360
we won, right?

558
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:14,600
Not yet.

559
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:18,120
Mr. Pitak just told me
Mr. Thee's got the program we sent.

560
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:21,800
Mr. Thee will set up a date for us
to take him on our program's tour

561
00:45:21,880 --> 00:45:23,200
to assess us and decide.

562
00:45:24,480 --> 00:45:26,000
Why are there so many steps?

563
00:45:26,520 --> 00:45:29,600
He should be able to decide
just with our company name alone.

564
00:45:31,400 --> 00:45:32,720
According to Mr. Pitak,

565
00:45:32,800 --> 00:45:35,200
A Round Trip Travel had to do the same.

566
00:45:37,760 --> 00:45:39,400
Don't worry, Kuk.

567
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:42,240
I'll take good care of Mr. Thee.

568
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:44,640
I won't let Mook win.

569
00:45:52,240 --> 00:45:58,000
PIAMSUK ORPHANAGE

570
00:46:04,320 --> 00:46:05,160
Here!

571
00:46:08,920 --> 00:46:10,840
Why did you want to come here?

572
00:46:14,200 --> 00:46:15,480
Mr. Thee.

573
00:46:21,000 --> 00:46:24,560
Just to let you know,
I only did the basic arrangements.

574
00:46:24,640 --> 00:46:27,720
I didn't ask for a formal welcome
or a ceremony

575
00:46:27,800 --> 00:46:30,000
because I know
you like to keep it private,

576
00:46:30,080 --> 00:46:32,160
and you don't like a big fuss.

577
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:38,120
Great customer analysis.

578
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:43,160
Wait in the car.

579
00:46:44,080 --> 00:46:45,080
I'm sorry?

580
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:49,720
Didn't you just tell me
I don't like a big fuss?

581
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:52,400
But I'm your guide.

582
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:56,160
For this place, no guide is needed.

583
00:47:04,600 --> 00:47:06,840
So you brought me along, for what?

584
00:47:10,120 --> 00:47:13,280
- Thee!
- Hello. What about the others?

585
00:47:13,360 --> 00:47:15,880
- They're inside.
- Let's go.

586
00:47:21,560 --> 00:47:24,200
You're too kind, Mrs. Prao.

587
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:27,240
You've always got a gift for us.

588
00:47:28,360 --> 00:47:29,960
I never saw you up close before.

589
00:47:30,040 --> 00:47:32,200
You're as pretty as all the moms said.

590
00:47:32,800 --> 00:47:35,400
My family happens to know
the CEO of that place.

591
00:47:36,000 --> 00:47:37,720
You can take
your kids there for a vacation.

592
00:47:38,480 --> 00:47:39,800
I will.

593
00:47:40,440 --> 00:47:43,840
Uh, didn't Mr. Anapat come with you today?

594
00:47:46,720 --> 00:47:49,520
Well, work's quite busy for him lately.

595
00:47:51,480 --> 00:47:53,120
Don't take this the wrong way,

596
00:47:53,720 --> 00:47:56,720
but I suggest you come here more often.

597
00:47:56,800 --> 00:48:00,480
That way, the other parents
can understand who's who.

598
00:48:02,080 --> 00:48:04,040
I didn't want to tell you this,

599
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:07,440
but there's a mom who likes to act

600
00:48:08,080 --> 00:48:10,640
as if she wants to be Poonpun's mom too.

601
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,040
And who's that?

602
00:48:15,120 --> 00:48:18,400
Well, it's Mook,
Kongkwan's mom, of course.

603
00:48:19,320 --> 00:48:24,320
It's true! That woman
acts overly familiar with Poonpun's dad.

604
00:48:27,280 --> 00:48:29,040
It's probably nothing.

605
00:48:29,120 --> 00:48:31,320
She's the manager at Pat's company.

606
00:48:32,400 --> 00:48:33,760
It won't be easy for her,

607
00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:35,960
even if she wants to be more than that.

608
00:48:36,040 --> 00:48:37,760
Pat has standards, you know.

609
00:48:41,360 --> 00:48:42,760
Grandma!

610
00:48:52,160 --> 00:48:54,760
- Hello, Grandma.
- Mommy's got work today,

611
00:48:54,840 --> 00:48:55,960
so I came to pick you up.

612
00:48:56,040 --> 00:48:57,840
- Are you hungry?
- Yes, I am!

613
00:48:57,920 --> 00:49:00,480
I made a bunch of food for you. Let's go.

614
00:49:09,200 --> 00:49:10,600
You'll get to ride it soon.

615
00:49:10,680 --> 00:49:14,160
See? See?

616
00:49:14,680 --> 00:49:16,160
Wonderful.

617
00:49:16,760 --> 00:49:19,360
- Okay.
- Yay!

618
00:49:19,440 --> 00:49:21,120
- I'll bring it there.
- Go try it.

619
00:49:24,800 --> 00:49:25,920
Who's going to ride it?

620
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:27,880
- Go do a test-ride.
- Ride it! Ride it!

621
00:49:27,960 --> 00:49:29,480
- Try it.
- Let's go.

622
00:49:30,240 --> 00:49:31,400
Careful, okay?

623
00:49:33,840 --> 00:49:36,560
Three, two, one.

624
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:38,400
Can I talk to you for a bit?

625
00:49:38,480 --> 00:49:39,400
Sure.

626
00:49:44,360 --> 00:49:45,200
What's up, Whan?

627
00:49:45,280 --> 00:49:48,000
<i>I finished arranging</i>
<i>the special program for tonight.</i>

628
00:49:48,080 --> 00:49:50,120
<i>The client will be pleased for sure.</i>

629
00:49:50,200 --> 00:49:53,320
Great work. Can you guys stay on standby?

630
00:49:53,400 --> 00:49:54,920
Just in case something happens.

631
00:49:55,440 --> 00:49:58,920
Our client's so bipolar. So unpredictable.

632
00:49:59,440 --> 00:50:00,480
<i>Okay!</i>

633
00:50:01,640 --> 00:50:02,760
Thank you.

634
00:50:19,800 --> 00:50:20,920
Come on in, Mr. Thee.

635
00:50:28,040 --> 00:50:30,440
I prepared a special show for you.

636
00:50:30,520 --> 00:50:33,000
I'm sure you'll be impressed.

637
00:50:38,160 --> 00:50:39,320
Are you shy?

638
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:45,320
I understand.

639
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:48,320
You must not get to go out
in the way that you want so often.

640
00:50:48,920 --> 00:50:52,080
So, enjoy yourself. I'll be outside,
so you won't feel uncomfortable.

641
00:50:52,160 --> 00:50:53,360
Where are you going?

642
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:58,080
I'll be waiting at a coffee shop nearby.

643
00:50:58,160 --> 00:51:00,000
You can stay here as long as you'd like.

644
00:51:00,840 --> 00:51:02,760
It's fine. You don't have to wait.

645
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:06,400
We'll go in together.

646
00:51:07,120 --> 00:51:08,880
Mr. Thee. Hey!

647
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:17,240
Oh, hey! I'm here, sis.

648
00:51:17,320 --> 00:51:20,000
Ooh, he's so hot!

649
00:51:20,080 --> 00:51:21,400
Do you have a reservation?

650
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:24,880
Uh, for A Round Trip Travel.

651
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:28,480
All done. I booked a table
and put it on the program.

652
00:51:29,000 --> 00:51:31,600
Thank you. Let's see.

653
00:51:34,920 --> 00:51:35,960
Mook.

654
00:51:37,000 --> 00:51:39,640
Um… Is Mr. Thee…

655
00:51:40,360 --> 00:51:43,760
You know, is he really… that type of guy?

656
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:47,360
I don't know either,

657
00:51:47,440 --> 00:51:51,480
but this is what the client's requested,
so we must oblige.

658
00:51:52,200 --> 00:51:55,200
Our client may be picky, snarky,

659
00:51:55,280 --> 00:51:57,040
and not so good with people,

660
00:51:57,640 --> 00:52:00,280
but we need to prove
our company's professionalism to him.

661
00:52:00,920 --> 00:52:02,120
Got it.

662
00:52:03,320 --> 00:52:04,600
Oh, Whan,

663
00:52:04,680 --> 00:52:07,800
I want to include
something special to impress him.

664
00:52:07,880 --> 00:52:09,120
- Special…
- Got any ideas?

665
00:52:11,920 --> 00:52:14,440
This place hosts
a special show for VIP guests.

666
00:52:14,520 --> 00:52:16,240
I booked the show already.

667
00:52:16,320 --> 00:52:18,120
Once Mr. Thee's done watching the show,

668
00:52:18,200 --> 00:52:20,400
he'll definitely sign a contract with us.

669
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:21,840
Perfect.

670
00:52:21,920 --> 00:52:25,360
Then I want it to be very special.

671
00:52:25,440 --> 00:52:26,440
Go all out.

672
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:28,640
You got it, Mook.

673
00:52:30,680 --> 00:52:32,080
VIP lounge and a special show…

674
00:52:33,240 --> 00:52:34,080
Upstairs, please.

675
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:40,440
Go ahead, Mr. Thee.

676
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:50,520
You've never been here?

677
00:52:53,040 --> 00:52:55,680
Why would a woman like me come here?

678
00:52:57,880 --> 00:52:59,320
And I thought you knew it all.

679
00:53:04,400 --> 00:53:05,440
Here we go.

680
00:53:39,640 --> 00:53:40,920
Not me!

681
00:54:10,760 --> 00:54:14,000
Alright. Long show, huh?

682
00:54:22,760 --> 00:54:23,840
‪Thank you.

683
00:54:29,320 --> 00:54:32,560
Thank you, Thee. It's been a while.

684
00:54:37,680 --> 00:54:38,760
You know him?

685
00:54:40,120 --> 00:54:42,120
Tony used to study abroad with me,

686
00:54:42,640 --> 00:54:45,320
but he prefers this life,
so he came back to work in Thailand.

687
00:54:47,040 --> 00:54:48,720
That's why you chose this place.

688
00:54:50,040 --> 00:54:53,400
I even asked Tony to put on
a very special show for you.

689
00:54:54,800 --> 00:54:56,400
I can't believe you.

690
00:54:57,480 --> 00:55:00,320
Let's go home. I had a lot of fun today.

691
00:55:02,280 --> 00:55:03,400
Mr. Thee!

692
00:55:18,760 --> 00:55:21,320
Well, aren't you cute?

693
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:24,320
Are you single?

694
00:55:27,520 --> 00:55:28,920
Hey, excuse me.

695
00:55:32,840 --> 00:55:33,920
What?

696
00:55:34,520 --> 00:55:36,040
- Are you crazy?
- What?

697
00:55:36,120 --> 00:55:36,960
What was that?

698
00:55:41,480 --> 00:55:43,200
You better go find your face

699
00:55:43,280 --> 00:55:45,760
- 'cause girl, you lost it.
- How embarrassing.

700
00:55:49,160 --> 00:55:50,240
Mr. Thee,

701
00:55:52,120 --> 00:55:54,880
- why did you do that?
- Do what?

702
00:55:54,960 --> 00:55:59,600
What? Well, what'd you kiss me for?

703
00:56:00,840 --> 00:56:03,000
The situation called for it.

704
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:06,040
If I didn't kiss you,
that person would've kissed me.

705
00:56:07,080 --> 00:56:10,120
And if I had to choose,
I'd rather kiss an auntie like you.

706
00:56:10,920 --> 00:56:11,840
Auntie?

707
00:56:12,680 --> 00:56:14,120
You're calling me an auntie?

708
00:56:16,400 --> 00:56:18,280
What else should I call you?

709
00:56:19,800 --> 00:56:21,800
Mook. Ms. Mook.

710
00:56:22,400 --> 00:56:25,080
Sister Mook. Anything.

711
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:28,080
You brought me here,

712
00:56:28,160 --> 00:56:31,760
so you're responsible
for any danger I may face.

713
00:56:32,320 --> 00:56:34,640
Isn't that the duty of a good guide,

714
00:56:35,360 --> 00:56:36,400
Auntie Mook?

715
00:56:47,200 --> 00:56:49,560
<i>Please dress appropriately.</i>

716
00:56:49,640 --> 00:56:53,280
<i>Show some respect</i>
<i>for the place and for me.</i>

717
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:01,240
I'm so sorry.

718
00:57:04,320 --> 00:57:05,920
Have we met before?

719
00:57:09,360 --> 00:57:10,960
Don't leave me.

720
00:57:13,040 --> 00:57:14,680
Don't leave me.

721
00:57:15,280 --> 00:57:16,800
Don't leave me.

722
00:57:18,240 --> 00:57:19,680
Boss. Boss--

723
00:57:21,760 --> 00:57:22,640
Boss!

724
00:57:23,840 --> 00:57:25,240
How could you do this, Mr. Thee?

725
00:57:25,320 --> 00:57:26,480
You're not a gentleman!

726
00:57:26,560 --> 00:57:27,440
What are you talking about?

727
00:58:18,840 --> 00:58:21,160
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
